alert.note: Alert for Gadsden; Liberty (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 12 at 1:56PM EDT until May 12 at 2:30PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a * Severe Thunderstorm Warning for... Southwestern Gadsden County in Big Bend of Florida... Northeastern Liberty County in Big Bend of Florida... * Until 230 PM EDT. * At 155 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles southwest of Greensboro, or 12 miles northeast of Blountstown, moving southeast at 10 mph. HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees. * Locations impacted include... Greensboro, Bristol, Telogia, Rock Bluff, Juniper, Sycamore, Hosford, Lowry, Wetumpka, Roy, Clio and Sawdust. HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH
info.instruction: For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a building.
